title: 'I'm extremely proud of them' - Father and husband of British-Israelis killed in West Bank calls for peace
description: The father and husband of three British-Israelis murdered in the West Bank this month has told Sky News that he is immensely proud of his wife and daughters, and called on the international community to come together to bring peace between Israelis and Palestinians.

title: Crisis talks underway to halt Sudan violence as more than 50 people killed
description: Crisis mediation is underway to de-escalate the armed violence in Sudan after at least 56 people were killed and almost 600 injured.

title: Japanese leader vows to tighten security for G7 after smoke bomb
description: The Japanese prime minister has vowed to tighten security for a series of G7 meetings taking place in the coming weeks.

title: Greek god of love and sex riding a dolphin among artefacts unearthed from ancient city's temple
description: Artefacts from an ancient Greek city dating back more than 2,000 years have been identified for the first time.

title: Why violence has erupted in Sudan
description: Fighting erupted in Sudan on Saturday as the army and paramilitary forces clashed, leaving at least 56 people dead and hundreds injured.

title: South Korea's military fires warning shots at North Korean vessel
description: South Korea's military has fired warning shots towards a North Korean patrol vessel amid heightened tensions over Kim Jong Un's latest missile test.

title: Fire in Dubai apartment building kills 16
description: A fire has ripped through an apartment building in Dubai, killing 16 people and injuring a further nine, authorities have said.

title: Six adults and child, 7, killed in shooting at Mexican holiday resort
description: Seven people, including a seven-year-old child, were killed when gunmen stormed a holiday resort in Mexico.

title: Indian gangster-turned-politician shot dead on live television
description: An Indian gangster-turned-politician has been shot dead on live television.

title: Germany shuts down its final three nuclear power plants, but govt admits plan has downsides
description: Germany has begun shutting down its three remaining nuclear power plants as part of a long-planned transition towards renewable energy.
